			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">(this is about my rogue, not my necro, but the rogue boards don't actually provide a place for stories, so hope y'all don't mind.  Shaddowe thinks more like  a dark elf than most of my dark elves do anyhow *grins*)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Once, when they had actually noticed she was there, they had told her she had not cried when she was born. There was a tinge of, well...not pride, but expectation in their voices. Shaddowe never complained, never spoke up, this is what they knew of her. Why then should they be proud of her for being what she was? A quiet child, a plain child, her only outstanding feature being her eyes, eyes that seemed to shift in color, green to blue to brown, eyes that took up half her face it seemed, and followed everyone, everywhere they went in a room. Observant, silent, unnoticed. 
<br />

<br />
She remembered sitting by herself with foraged berries for supper because they had forgotten her again. She recalled watching others pick their apprenticeships, go off to learn their trades, but what could Shaddowe do? She hardly remembered her real name anymore, they never used it. She followed them around silently, often unnoticed until they tripped over her. It was a joke to some... Got your shadow following you again? ...but she took that as her name, it never occured to her to ask to be called anything else, she asked them nothing. Her voice was rarely heard, even by herself. 
<br />

<br />
So what to do with her life? What were her choices? Here, there were trainers for only so much: the path of the bard, the ranger, the druid, the warrior...the rogue. The choice had been easy. She had no skill for magic, nor particular affinity for nature, so that ruled out ranger and druid. There was no way you would catch her rushing headlong into battle, the small thin girl who would hardly scare a child, let alone any opponent. And who would listen to songs played by one who they didn't even notice most of the time? So... a rogue. That one was easy. She was a shadow anyway, wasn't she? 
<br />

<br />
She had only just picked her path, when he came, a human, though she was not sure what he was at first, she had never seen one. She had been back against a railing again, watching, unnoticed and unseen by most, but he had turned his silvery blue eyes on her... and beckoned, a smile like an angel's curving his lips. And he had known her name. 
<br />

<br />
"Come to me, Shaddowe...let me take you from here. I will care for you, protect you..." And as easily as that, she had followed. He had seen to it that she was outfitted, a rogue she had never seen stepping from the shadows with a bag for her... the first things she had ever been given. And then they were gone... and the forest she had called home was left far behind. She hadn't thought to say goodbye, she was not sure if they would even notice... 
<br />

<br />
He had brought her to Freeport, a city of humans, and told her to stay nearby, and train, and grow... he would be watching, and he would come back. She had found a place to train, and learned her craft, working hard, not sleeping, hoping the faster she advanced, the sooner she would hear that voice again. But the time grew longer, and all she heard of him were brief whispers on the wind. No one else talked to her, but she was not surprised, no one ever had. She had tried talking to herself a few times, but her voice was hoarse and rusty from disuse, and it was easier to just hold conversations in her mind. 
<br />

<br />
Then she had seen them. Walking through the Eastern Commonlands, towards a small tunnel leading into Nektulos Forest, a place she had been told never to go, she saw the most beautiful creatures she had ever seen. Indigo skin, flowing white hair.. what were they? It had taken all of her courage to open her mouth and ask... 
<br />
</span><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
