			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-style: italic">Shaddowe crept into Neriak under the cover of darkness, hiding in shadows, still uncertain of the powers of her new mask. A simple spell, a few words said, and the mask was firmly in place. She could feel the change immediately. Gathering her courage, and tensing, should she need to run, she stepped out of the shadows and walked towards the guards. They nodded at her in disinterested acceptance, and she walked through into this town. She had made it! 
<br />

<br />
After all the stories she had heard of the nasty, vicious tier'dal as a child, she had never thought she would even dream of coming here, to their home. Fier'dal children were raised to hate and fear the dark ones, twisted, evil beings worshipping the Prince of Hate, Innoruuk himself. She was no different, but then she had seen them. Beautiful, graceful creatures, cunning and deadly... vibrant in a way that she had never seen. They lived life to its fullest, and died the same way, without reservation or fear. Their dusky indigo skin and flowing white hair so alien to her, where all had tanned ruddy complexions, and most were brunette or blonde. Ordinary... fier'dal were ordinary. It was how she had always felt. But the tier'dal.. so exotic, so open in their sensuality. That is what she had wanted to be. 
<br />

<br />
And so she had learned of the mask, and risked much to get it. Wandering deep into Innothule, a place where her kind was considered a good meal, sneaking all the way into the bowels of Guk, where should she make a misstep she would surely perish, she came across a wizard and knight who were willing to help her, who knew who held this mask. The wizard surprisingly was tier'dal, but did not turn on the young wood elf, as Shaddowe had expected. And she was somehow familiar. She reminded Shaddowe of the man who had brought her here from her homeland. Funny, that... 
<br />

<br />
The knight was a human, more than willing to help her, and quite kind. She smiled in excitement at the thought that what she longed for was so within reach. The pair laughed and talked, slaughtering the frogloks as she watched fascinated, then suddenly, a laugh of triumph. "Shaddowe, come get your mask, and let us leave!" She grabbed it, clutching it to her and the wizardess cast a spell transporting them through time and space, to land almost instantly at the wizard pyramid in Nektulos Forest. Shaddowe giggled and tried the mask on. Somehow, instinctively in wearing it, she knew its secrets, and a few words rolled off her tongue, the transformation almost instant. She looked down at indigo skinned hands, when she pulled her hair forward, it was a long snow white mass... "I am... tier'dal?" They smiled and nodded at her. To the young rogue, it was a dream come true. She had not fit in among her own people, perhaps among these... and now for the test. She thanked them both heartily and headed towards Neriak... </span><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
