			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ahh, but that had been many years ago. In the manner of elves, she would live for centuries, and still appeared to be quite young. It had taken a long time however, for her to hone the skills that made her such a deadly assassin, it had not come overnight. She had met the wizardess again, when the woman pulled her aside in Neriak one day, startling the young rogue. Shaddowe wore a badge now, had joined one of the smaller qu’ellaren through deception and intrigue, enjoying the game and never thinking beyond today. 
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">The voice came from the shadows after watching the rogue pick up the dropped V'umbra badge. 
<br />

<br />
"I see you are putting that mask to good use, jalil." 
<br />

<br />
The wizard moved closer to the girl, knowing she had a small amount of her trust. It had been nothing to help her recieve her guise in the depths of Lower Guk, in fact, it had been fun. It had been some time since she had praticed her magic ways in a dungeon of any sort. 
<br />

<br />
Tarabella ran a finger over the badge now pinned to Shaddowe's chest. The rogue moved backwards a bit, visibly startled by the wizard's presence. 
<br />

<br />
"You best be wise, jalil, when wearing that badge. They would be quick to kill you if they learn of your duplicity." 
<br />

<br />
She used her thoughts to permeate the girls mind, communicating in the safest way possible. 
<br />

<br />
’This is the Third Gate, Shaddowe, where all the darkest of magics are practiced, as well as your craft. It is also home to the library, where I study often.’ 
<br />

<br />
The wizard's visage softened. "Come, let us leave this place. I would love to hear what you think of Neriak...and how you have been welcomed." </span>
<br />

<br />
Shaddowe smiled a moment in reverie, then shook it off. The wizardess had taught her many useful lessons: the tier’dal language, their customs and religion…and who the man had been, the one who had taken her from Kelethin so long ago. Vampyre! Even now, the word could send shivers down her spine. Had she been meant as a meal? Or as one of his flock? She might never know...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
