			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Shaddowe awoke from a troubled dream, still sure that she could hear that voice reverberating through her head... his voice. And she could hear Gratis as well, telling her what he was, Aquaenus... her benefactor, the one who had taken her away from the trees... Vampire! But he was also a father figure, the first man who had taken notice of the slight fier'dal, the painfully shy girl of the shadows. She somehow could not fear him. 
<br />

<br />
It had been years now, since he left her in Freeport. She no longer hoped for or feared his return. She was used to being forgotten, and assumed that he had forgotten as well. But the sound of his voice still haunted her. 
<br />

<br />
It was just as well, for the Priest would not have recognized her. She strode with a purpose now, she carried herself with a sense of self-pride, and was rarely unnoticed. Never once had she returned to see the place of her birth, it had been left behind, along with her self-doubt and insecurity. She was a woman who had travelled far in her life. She had left Freeport, and settled in a new home... Neriak, home to the tier'dal. She no longer needed her Mask of the Deceiver, she could walk through most of Neriak unmolested, and the few who had refused to accept her, rarely got the opportunity to see her. Those same eyes still dominated her face, but these days they were full of an amused and sometimes calculating gleam. She had hunted and stolen a veritable treasure trove of items, and was a wealthy woman in her own right. 
<br />

<br />
"No, Aquaenus, you would not recognize the little broken sparrow you rescued... for I have grown into a bird of prey..." she whispered softly to herself in amusement, before sliding from her bed and, suddenly feeling restless, dressing quickly and leaving the Keep in search of trouble. 
<br />

<br />
She had been leaving the Keep more and more, feeling as if the walls were closing in on her. Many of her close friends had left the guildhall permanently, and she spent much time debating to herself what to do. This place had been her home for so long…not her first home though. Her first home had been a small tier’dal house, where she had found one like herself...<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
