			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some months later, the memory of that conversation had the girl laughing bitterly at her gullibility. Gratis had left, apparently he had found her quite ordinary after all. She had been discovered, and chased from Qu'ellar V'Umbra. Thank Innoruuk she had curried enough favor with the city that they did not kill her on the spot. The soft vulnerable young girl had changed. Time, circumstances... what the cause was did not matter. She did not dare go home now. And honestly, why would she wish to? She had become an assassin, not a scout, as most fier'dal rogues became, but someone who killed for gain. She had killed her own kind without batting a lash, killed both good and evil, deserving and not. Needs must.. she thought grimly. And she had needed... needed to forget, needed to move on, to change who she was. That girl was buried so deep now, she might never emerge.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
