			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Men had never been a problem since she came into her own, women either come to think of it. She had had almost any she wanted, even if she wasn’t perhaps the most beautiful woman. When she thought about it at all, she figured it was her confidence. Nothing shook her anymore. She no longer questioned her appearance, her skills, anything. One man had said it was her walk, that she strolled in looking like she owned the place, and everyone in it. She had liked the sentiment, but unfortunately, he had been one of her assignments, and that night had been his last. 
<br />

<br />
It was amazing the number of men who could be fooled by supple curves and a pretty face. Even those men who knew what she was arrogantly went with her, sure that they could so impress her that she would not kill them, or perhaps that they could overpower her if she tried. It was not like she killed every man she slept with, or slept with every man she killed, but it was always an easy lure for her prey. Those who had been with her and lived only made others more determined to be able to say they’d had her as well, and her task kept getting easier. Then there were those who didn’t brag, didn’t boast their conquests about Neriak. Those were the ones she called friends. 
<br />

<br />
For all the tier’dal attitude about “lesser races”, they pursued her most of all. She had taken two separate leaders of Neriak qu’ellaran as lovers at one point or another. Shadowknight, rogue, warrior… all had pursued her, or demanded her aquiesence, at one point or another. She just chose who she found pleasing. Those whose company she enjoyed, and who did not see it as a childish game, bragging to their friends like a little boy with a new toy, were allowed into the ranks of those who she called abbil. 
<br />

<br />
Only a few people made it to the inner circle however. Gratis, her first lover, the first and only man to ever hurt her. Leahali, a priestess she kept close to her heart. Tarabella, a wizard who had taught her much about who she was. There were others that came and went. They drifted in and out of her life, but she was always happy to see them. However, these three were her closest confidantes.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=738273" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v701/evileene/evilsig2.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
